  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 300°F (150°C).",
    "Season the lamb with salt and black pepper.",
    "Heat the olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the lamb pieces and sear until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the onion, garlic, and ginger to the pot and cook, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables are softened, about 8 minutes.",
    "Add the cumin, coriander, and cayenne pepper to the pot and cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.",
    "Add the treacle (if using) and 1 cup of water to the pot.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then cover the pot and transfer it to the preheated oven.",
    "Bake the tagine, covered, for 2 1/2 hours, or until the lamb is tender and the sauce has thickened.",
    "Remove the pot from the oven and stir in the chopped parsley.",
    "Serve the tagine hot, garnished with additional parsley if desired."
  ],
